ong> or <strong>Frances Fisher</strong>; instead it was the personal outrea=
ch from the campaign, the starry Q&amp;A hosts and tastemaker screenings, a=
nd the televised
endorsements from the likes of <strong>Cate Blanchett</strong> that fed <em=
>all</em> media. That=E2=80=99s what has always mattered most.=C2=A0=C2=A0=
=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-b=
ottom:0px;"><strong>=C2=A0</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;">So no, the A.=
I. in <em>The Brutalist </em>won=E2=80=99t lose it best picture, nor will t=
he cultural missteps in <em>Emilia P=C3=A9rez</em> (even that =E2=80=9Cpeni=
s to vagina=E2=80=9D song), or the lack of intimacy coordinators on <em>Ano=
ra</em>, or
