"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">Disney=E2=80=
=99s <em>Freaky Friday: Freakier Friday</em> is a pure nostalgia play that =
targets the grown-ups who made the <strong>Lindsay Lohan</strong>=E2=80=93<=
strong>Jamie Lee Curtis</strong> remake a hit more than 20 years ago. The s=
ame could be said of Paramount=E2=80=99s <em>Naked Gun</em> reboot, starrin=
g <strong>Liam Neeson</strong> and <strong>Pamela Anderson</strong>. Sony=
=E2=80=99s comedic <em>Anaconda</em> revamp, starring <strong>Jack
Black</strong> and <strong>Paul Rudd</strong>, could be another example of =
a studio scraping the bottom of the barrel for any past hit that could be r=
etrofitted into a franchise reboot. Sony, however, could potentially learn =
from its blockbuster <em>Jumanji</em> revival, and craft something <em>good=
 enough</em> to appeal to moviegoers who couldn=E2=80=99t care less about t=
he original. Along with Paramount=E2=80=99s planned <em>Scary Movie</em> re=
vival, these remakes could remind audiences that they used to show
up to theaters for the exclusive purpose of laughing for 90-120 minutes. (T=
his year also features legacy sequels of <em>Karate Kid </em>and <em>I Know=
 What You Did Last Summer</em>, but neither is a reboot or remake.)</p></di=
